				<P>SSRA might surprise you =)</P>
<P>It is up there with places like NToV for fun factor. The encounters are well designed and although the mobs are all pretty similar looking, there's enough atmosphere and lore for you to actually think "What have I done???" when you awaken the Cursed, Destroyer of Gods... The loot and droprate is also very good (especially for cursed cycle) and there are enough different targets of different difficulty that it will keep you busy for a while =) Recommend you start with Rhag cycle and work from there =)</P>
<P>VT key shard camp isn't as bad as people say. But VT itself really is as bad as people say. It's a very /yawn zone and not friendly to casuals because it takes a loooong time to clear.</P>
<P>Be sure to stop by in Griegs End at some point and kill Grieg Venecius. I love that zone =)</P>
